Definition: Old World annual having heart-shaped leaves and large seeds with short greyish lint removed with difficulty
Example: considered an ancestor of modern short-staple cottons
Synonyms: Gossypium_herbaceum, cotton, Old, World, annual, having, heart-shaped, leaves, and, large, seeds, with, short, greyish, lint, removed, difficulty, considered, an, ancestor, of, modern, short-staple, cottons
Category: noun.plant
